  Given an expected number of items `n` and a desired false-positive rate `p`,
  the optimal parameters are derived as:

      m = -ceil(n * ln(p) / ln(2)^2)   â€” number of bits
      k = round(m / n * ln(2))         â€” number of hash functions
  """

  @enforce_keys [:m, :k, :bits]
  defstruct [:m, :k, :bits]

  @type t :: %__MODULE__{
          m: pos_integer(),
          k: pos_integer(),
          bits: tuple()
